## SECTION 5: BONUS MUST-DO QUESTIONS (Questions 51-60) ⭐ VERY IMPORTANT

### Data-Oriented Questions (51-55)

51. Find mean, median, and mode of a list
    - Core for statistics & ML preprocessing

52. Normalize a list using Min-Max scaling
    - Formula: x' = (x - min) / (max - min)
    - Used in ML preprocessing

53. Standardize a list (Z-score normalization)
    - Formula: z = (x - μ) / σ
    - Important for ML models

54. Remove null / empty values from a list
    - Simulates real-world messy data handling

55. Handle outliers in a list (remove values beyond threshold)
    - Important for data cleaning in ML

### Dictionary & Frequency Questions (56-58)

56. Group elements by frequency
    - Example: [1,2,1,3,2] → {1:[0,2], 2:[1,4], 3:[3]}

57. Sort dictionary by values (descending)
    - Useful for ranking and sorting problems

58. Find top k frequent elements in a list
    - Common interview + ML preprocessing problem

### Logic & Real-world Questions (59-60)

59. Implement a simple log analyzer
    - Input: list of logs
    - Output: most frequent error type

60. Convert a list of dictionaries into a single dictionary
    - Example: [{"a":1}, {"b":2}] → {"a":1, "b":2}
    - Useful for data merging